statement:
\emph{Sketch a single function satisfying all of the listed criteria.}

\begin{enumerate}
\itemsep1pt\parskip0pt\parsep0pt
\item
  $\displaystyle f'(x) = kf(x)$ for some positive constant \emph{k}.
\end{enumerate}

sols:
Any exponential function of the form $f(x) = a^x$, where $a$ is a real
number, will satisfy the equation above because
$\displaystyle f'(x) = \ln(a)a^x = kf(x)$ for \emph{k = ln(a)}. One
example would be our favorite $f(x) = e^x$. Here \emph{k = ln(e) = 1}
